properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 30 at 1:27PM PST until January 31 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 50 mph.

* WHERE...San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland
Empire, San Bernardino County Mountains, Riverside County
Mountains, Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills and San Gorgonio
Pass Near Banning.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Dangerous travel for high profile vehicles. Gusty
winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be
blown down and a few power outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds are currently gusting near 30 mph,
and we don't anticipate winds to meet warning thresholds.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST FRIDAY... ...HIGH WIND WARNING IS CANCELLED
